               <msContents class="#STM">
                  <summary>  Tibétain 528 contains the Chinese woodblock print of the Sūtra of Noble Marīcī (<title xml:lang="bo">'phags ma 'od zer can ma zhes bya ba bzhugs sto</title>). The Chinese title is given on the right margin of each folio: Doumu jing 斗母經 [Mother of the Great Dipper] (in China, Marīcī is conflated with the Daoist goddess Doumu).</summary>
                  
