                    <p>The cover, composed of sturdy paper wrapped in silk, has an additional piece of red fabric glued to its center. This central fabric displays the Tibetan title in red ink, followed by the prayer, <term xml:lang="bo">bkra shis par gyur cig</term>, translating to "May there
be prosperity!" On the verso, the Buddha Śākyamuni and the Goddess Marīcī are represented respectively on
the left and the right, with namaskāras in the middle. The back cover portrays four
Dharmapālas. Notably, the entire text is printed in red ink.</p></binding>
